00:07:06.880 --> 00:07:08.080
If I wasn't desperate to deliver,

00:07:08.720 --> 00:07:10.080
I'd never splurge on a ride.

00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.080
I'm raising this kid alone,

00:07:12.480 --> 00:07:14.160
I can't leave him home alone,

00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:15.920
so I bring him along on runs.

00:07:16.760 --> 00:07:17.560
I just don't get it.

00:07:18.880 --> 00:07:20.080
Why is life this hard?

00:07:23.640 --> 00:07:24.160
I really feel like

00:07:24.160 --> 00:07:25.640
I'm already doing my best.

00:08:09.440 --> 00:08:10.120
Ailing,

00:08:10.480 --> 00:08:12.160
I'm dropping some things off.

00:08:12.400 --> 00:08:13.320
If you're not home

00:08:13.320 --> 00:08:14.360
I'll leave them at your door,

00:08:14.520 --> 00:08:15.560
so you can take them in later.

00:08:22.120 --> 00:08:23.200
Hurry up.

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:25.320
Give me a small one.

00:08:25.320 --> 00:08:26.600
There's only room for one more.

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:29.600
Ailing.

00:08:30.600 --> 00:08:30.880
Sister.

00:08:31.080 --> 00:08:32.240
Where are you going?

00:08:33.559 --> 00:08:34.360
Why are you here?

00:08:34.919 --> 00:08:36.440
To bring you some things.

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:38.960
Where are you off to?

00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:40.520
We're...

00:08:41.480 --> 00:08:42.159
- Going out.
- Moving.

00:08:56.680 --> 00:08:58.760
You sold your home ten years ago?

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:01.880
If I hadn't run into you today,

00:09:02.240 --> 00:09:03.240
were you planning to keep this

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:04.200
from me for another 10 or 20 years,

00:09:04.200 --> 00:09:05.560
or your whole life?

00:09:08.360 --> 00:09:09.480
You clearly don't see me

00:09:09.480 --> 00:09:10.080
as your sister.

00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:13.960
Back when you were at teachers' college,

00:09:15.680 --> 00:09:17.480
you came to me about everything.

00:09:20.120 --> 00:09:22.400
Exams, graduation,

00:09:22.400 --> 00:09:23.360
boyfriends.

00:09:24.280 --> 00:09:25.280
Back then

00:09:25.280 --> 00:09:26.280
you weren't financially independent,

00:09:26.760 --> 00:09:28.640
felt you lived off me, right?

00:09:30.160 --> 00:09:31.600
You can fly on your own now

00:09:31.760 --> 00:09:32.760
and I'm retired,

00:09:32.760 --> 00:09:33.760
so I can't help much anymore.

00:09:34.600 --> 00:09:36.080
Selling the flat's a big thing,

00:09:36.080 --> 00:09:37.600
and you wouldn't even consult me?

00:09:37.600 --> 00:09:38.560
You don't even have a place

00:09:38.560 --> 00:09:39.240
that's truly your own.

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:40.480
How did your life end up

00:09:40.480 --> 00:09:41.480
like this?

00:09:47.400 --> 00:09:48.240
I'm sorry.

00:09:58.000 --> 00:10:00.040
I shouldn't scold you now.

00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:02.520
Don't cry.

00:10:08.720 --> 00:10:09.400
Please.

00:10:11.640 --> 00:10:13.320
If Mom could see you like this,

00:10:13.440 --> 00:10:14.600
she'd blame me.

00:10:16.320 --> 00:10:17.280
I'm sorry.

00:10:17.480 --> 00:10:19.120
I haven't been paying attention to you.

00:10:31.120 --> 00:10:31.800
Where've you been?

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:44.280
I tried to find you this morning

00:10:44.520 --> 00:10:45.200
but you were swamped.

00:10:45.920 --> 00:10:46.640
Went looking for you this afternoon

00:10:46.640 --> 00:10:47.480
and you were gone again.

00:10:48.600 --> 00:10:49.280
Let me ask you,

00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:50.480
why did you tell Zhang Ran

00:10:50.480 --> 00:10:51.560
about me and Fu Yongjun?

00:10:52.120 --> 00:10:53.600
Now everyone's awkward.

00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.280
From now on,

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:55.880
don't

00:10:56.440 --> 00:10:57.440
tell her family stuff, okay?

00:11:12.080 --> 00:11:14.240
I saw you at the Chinese supermarket

00:11:14.240 --> 00:11:14.920
last week.

00:11:15.160 --> 00:11:16.160
You had two kids with you.

00:11:17.280 --> 00:11:18.240
Then why didn't you call out to me?

00:11:18.760 --> 00:11:20.040
I didn't want to bother you.

00:11:21.080 --> 00:11:22.240
Nonsense.

00:11:24.240 --> 00:11:25.120
I noticed your daughter

00:11:25.120 --> 00:11:26.320
looks just like you.

00:11:27.120 --> 00:11:27.640
Yeah.

00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:29.040
You've never heard that?

00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:30.160
Daughters take after their dads,

00:11:30.160 --> 00:11:31.160
sons take after their moms.

00:11:33.120 --> 00:11:34.320
But my girl's temper

00:11:34.320 --> 00:11:35.320
is more like her mother.

00:11:36.480 --> 00:11:37.560
She doesn't talk much,

00:11:37.560 --> 00:11:38.840
a bit icy.

00:11:39.160 --> 00:11:40.760
You're not much of a talker either.

00:11:42.040 --> 00:11:43.200
Oh, come on.

00:11:43.520 --> 00:11:45.800
I think I can chatter

00:11:46.160 --> 00:11:47.160
- non-stop.
- Since when?

00:11:49.440 --> 00:11:50.960
Depends who I'm with, I guess.

00:11:51.440 --> 00:11:52.160
Sometimes

00:11:52.160 --> 00:11:52.920
you see certain people

00:11:52.920 --> 00:11:54.840
and you just can't think of

00:11:54.840 --> 00:11:55.760
a single word to say.

00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:00.280
Back when my wife and I

00:12:00.280 --> 00:12:01.320
were home,

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:02.280
we'd each

00:12:02.640 --> 00:12:03.920
curl up with a book,

00:12:04.680 --> 00:12:05.480
sit in

00:12:06.720 --> 00:12:08.440
our own corners

00:12:09.000 --> 00:12:09.880
all afternoon

00:12:10.840 --> 00:12:12.280
without saying a word.

00:12:12.680 --> 00:12:13.240
But just knowing

00:12:13.240 --> 00:12:14.800
someone else is in the room with you,

00:12:15.840 --> 00:12:17.040
that feels pretty good.

00:12:19.880 --> 00:12:21.440
A cup of coffee, a book,

00:12:21.920 --> 00:12:23.000
and a whole day like that,

00:12:23.520 --> 00:12:24.080
sounds perfect.

00:12:27.840 --> 00:12:28.800
But when she

00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:30.480
asked for a divorce,

00:12:30.480 --> 00:12:31.040
she said

00:12:34.160 --> 00:12:35.120
she wanted a life

00:12:35.640 --> 00:12:37.320
with real everyday warmth.

00:12:37.320 --> 00:12:40.040
A life where you can actually argue.

00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:46.400
She likes arguing?

00:12:47.720 --> 00:12:49.720
It's not what you think.

00:12:49.720 --> 00:12:51.040
Sometimes arguing

00:12:51.040 --> 00:12:52.480
is just another way of talking.

00:12:54.320 --> 00:12:56.080
What I mean is that

00:12:57.960 --> 00:13:00.080
if two people can still fight,

00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:02.000
nothing truly huge has broken yet.

00:13:02.720 --> 00:13:05.000
When you can't even fight anymore,

00:13:05.600 --> 00:13:06.920
that's when things are really bad.

00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:24.320
You're that hot-and-sour noodles girl,

00:13:24.320 --> 00:13:24.640
right?

00:13:28.840 --> 00:13:29.520
I ordered in your live stream.

00:13:31.280 --> 00:13:31.920
Thanks.

00:13:32.760 --> 00:13:34.480
Online you're so loud and bouncy.

00:13:35.040 --> 00:13:37.080
In real life you're pretty quiet.

00:13:39.320 --> 00:13:40.760
Because you don't know me yet.

00:13:58.280 --> 00:13:59.000
It's so late

00:13:59.000 --> 00:13:59.920
and you're still on the road?

00:14:01.760 --> 00:14:03.400
Once I drop you off, I'm done.

00:14:04.080 --> 00:14:05.440
Wife and kid are waiting at home.

00:16:17.080 --> 00:16:17.800
Coming.

00:16:28.400 --> 00:16:29.080
Coming.

00:16:30.240 --> 00:16:31.640
No, no, don't jump.

